article.description: John Carter Jr. and Cam Davis scored 24 points apiece as Navy defeated Cornell 72-61 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Navy tops Cornell 72-61 behind Carter, Davis
article.linkText: Navy tops Cornell 72-61 behind Carter, Davis
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- John Carter Jr. and Cam Davis scored 24 points apiece as Navy defeated Cornell 72-61 on Tuesday night. Greg Summers had 12 points and 12 rebounds for Navy (3-3), ahich led 42-29 at halftime. Jimmy Boeheim had 18 points and 11 rebounds for the Big Red (1-6), who have now lost six straight games. Terrance McBride added 12 points. Navy matches up against Brown on the road on Saturday. Cornell matches up against Towson at home on Sunday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
